					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Xott's Box 1</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=573575" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Greetings Lore readers.
<p>
I've spent my fair share of time on Norrath, and I believe that it is a benefit to us all, if from time to time; I share what I have seen and heard, in order to make Norrath more enjoyable for everyone.  My words will range from opinions, and ideas to stories and myths and will all be open for debate, and comments, and of course, my e-mail is open to you all for the same reasons.  This is an opinion collumn, so don't think I'm claiming to be all knowing.  :o)
<p>
As an introduction, I'd like to touch on GM events, and the etiquette that we should all try to maintain, if not to enjoy the event, to allow those who would like to, do so.
<p>
If your not interested, go back to what you were doing, and ignore the event.  There is nothing more irritating, then a player who fills /shout and /ooc with negative comments about the event, Verant, or the people trying to run the event.  You’re a nuisance, not funny.
<p>
If you are interested, knowing when to talk, shout and roleplay, and when to sit and listen, will help things run along a lot smoother.  If 70 players are filling the channels with nonsense, important shouts, and says will be missed, causing more and more confusion, and less fun.
<p>
Finally, training mobs, and NPCs into the event, (or out of depending on what the idea is) does nothing but ruin everyone’s fun, or at least those that may be KoS to the guards.  If you playing a game, to ruin other peoples fun, it's time to spend your 12.95 on something else.
<p>
I welcome your comments, questions, or flames to <a href="mailto:xott@everlore.com">xott@everlore.com</a>.  I'd also like to know what you think about me occasionally posting something of this nature.
<p>
Godspeed<br>
Xott of the Nexus
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
