			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, to start off, I'd like to know exactly what gives a person the right to tell other ppl how to play a game. Especially, a game that ppl play money for!<BR>
<BR>
 If a person's sole enjoyment from the game comes from going and ruining another person's day, then fine.. let them do it! DE's are by nature very mean spirited. And just because a person doesn't necissarily talk about their dieties while they train a bunch of NPCs onto you, doesn't mean that they don't have the right to do it.<BR>
<BR>
Now, I personally don't go around and try and make the game more difficult for others, but I'm not going to get upset just because some other person is being a jerk. Because, it's just a game!<BR>
Once you start censoring ppl's right to act they way they want, then all sorts of issues arise. <BR>
<BR>
What about the lowly Newb that doesn't understand what to do? Is he going to be kicked just because he doesn't know exactly how everyone else MUST have THEIR game played? I think it's incredibly stupid to try and focus energy on something you have no control over and really have no right to control in the first place.<BR>
<BR>
~Adden Thorneblade<BR>
Quellious
