				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Heh...Xott, as I said to you earlier...this is a good idea, but you probably should have started with just a simple &quot;This is what to expect&quot; type instead of jumping right into it.<BR>
<BR>
But, everyone else (in specific JA), everything that Xott said is right on.<BR>
<BR>
Now, JA...I will give you credit for flaming INTELLIGENTLY...you didn't resort to name calling, AND you gave reasons why you think Xott is wrong.  But I'm afraid, they weren't very good.<BR>
<BR>
Xott was simpling talking about politeness.  And anyone who plays EQ and delights in disrupting others, especially GMs trying to give an event or the players trying to enjoy it, needs to cancel their account and take some therapy meetings.<BR>
<BR>
How would those people, the ones that you are trying to defend, feel if they were at work and someone was over their shoulder screaming at them or throwing things at them (I'm equating that to training MOBs).  They shouldn't...and frankly, I would hope they would get pissed off.<BR>
<BR>
I don't give a rats ass how people enjoy the game.  They pay to play it, so they should enjoy it.  But, when that enjoyment comes at the expense of other's enjoyment and or people just doing their job (GMs - events are part of their job), then it's completely unacceptable.  I only wish more GMs/Guides had the courage/ability (some may not) to /kick anyone found disturbing their events.<BR>
<BR>
So, while you (JA) have a point - in that people have some (some, not complete) right to enjoy a game they pay for in the way they wish - there is a point where that right should be (and I wish it happened more often) removed/revoked.
